<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Australians will have to wait until at least December 17 to enjoy an overseas holiday after the government extended its coronavirus travel ban. </p>

<p>Health Minister Greg Hunt on Thursday said the decision was made on advice provided by the Australian Health Protection Principal Committee. </p>

<p>'AHPPC has advised that the international and domestic COVID-19 situation continues to pose an unacceptable public health risk,' he said.</p>

<p>'The extension of the emergency period is an appropriate response to that risk.'</p>

<p>More to come.  </p>
